# Demo Copilot — Cursor / Windsurf Rules
# This file is loaded automatically by Cursor and Windsurf as project context.

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
Demo Copilot is an AI pipeline that takes a web app URL and outputs a cinematic MP4 product demo video.
Pipeline: URL → Analyze → Script → Record (Playwright) → Voice (ElevenLabs) → Render (Remotion) → MP4

## MONOREPO LAYOUT
- apps/web     → Next.js 14 App Router, port 3000
- apps/api     → Fastify + BullMQ pipeline, port 3001
- packages/types → ALL shared TypeScript types (single source of truth)
- packages/db    → Prisma schema + generated client

## ABSOLUTE RULES
- Never duplicate types — always import from @demo-copilot/types
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow
- Never write LLM prompts inline — all prompts live in apps/api/src/modules/script/prompts.ts
- Never hardcode API keys or secrets
- Always validate LLM JSON output with Zod before using
- Always use isolated Playwright browser contexts per scene
- Run pnpm typecheck before marking any task done
- No default exports in the api app

## LLM MODEL
Always use: claude-sonnet-4-20250514
Client: @anthropic-ai/sdk

## LLM CALL PATTERN
```typescript
// Always wrap in retry loop, always validate with Zod
async function callLLM<T>(prompt: string, schema: z.ZodType<T>): Promise<T> {
  for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= 3; attempt++) {
    const response = await client.messages.create({
      model: "claude-sonnet-4-20250514",
      max_tokens: 4096,
      messages: [{ role: "user", content: prompt }],
    });
    const text = response.content[0].type === "text" ? response.content[0].text : "";
    const jsonMatch = text.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}|\[[\s\S]*\]/);
    if (!jsonMatch) continue;
    try { return schema.parse(JSON.parse(jsonMatch[0])); } catch {}
  }
  throw new Error("LLM failed after 3 attempts");
}
```

## PLAYWRIGHT PATTERN
- Always headless in production
- Always recordVideo per context
- Always isolate context per scene
- Always capture at 1920×1080
- Store segments as: OUTPUT_DIR/[projectId]/segments/scene-[id].mp4

## CODE STYLE
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- kebab-case.ts for all files
- PascalCase.tsx for all React components
- Named exports only in api
- Async/await everywhere (no .then chains)
- Zod for all external data (API inputs, LLM output)
- pino for logging in api, console for web

## DATABASE
- Prisma ORM only
- Client singleton at apps/api/src/lib/prisma.ts
- Never use raw SQL unless Prisma cannot do it

## API ROUTES
All prefixed /api/v1
- POST /projects           → create + queue
- GET  /projects           → list
- GET  /projects/:id       → detail + status
- GET  /projects/:id/status → SSE stream
- GET  /projects/:id/download → video URL redirect

## ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, ELEVENLABS_API_KEY,
ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID, OUTPUT_DIR, API_PORT, WEB_PORT, NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL

## PACKAGES (do not substitute)
api: fastify, bullmq, ioredis, playwright, @anthropic-ai/sdk, elevenlabs, fluent-ffmpeg, zod, prisma
web: next@14, zustand, @tanstack/react-query, framer-motion, tailwindcss

## BUILD ORDER (do not skip phases)
Phase 1 → Phase 2 → Phase 3 → Phase 4 → Phase 5
See tasks/PHASE_N.md for detailed task lists

